#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/nate/skills/marketing-and-growth/churn-prevention/references/cancel-flow-patterns.md savings=-1%
M|Canc|tx|Detailed cancel flow patterns by business tp, billing pr, and industry.
M|Canc|tx|---
M|B2C |tx|hi volume, lo touch. The flow must work w/o human intervention.
M|B2C |**Fl|**
M|B2C |tx|```
M|B2C |tx|Cancel button → Exit survey (1 question) → Dynamic offer → Confirm → Post-cancel
M|B2C |tx|```
M|B2C |**Ch|**
M|B2C |it|Fully automated, no human in the loop
M|B2C |it|Quick — 2-3 screens maximum
M|B2C |it|One offer + one fallback, not a menu of options
M|B2C |it|Mobile-optimized (sig cancellations on mobile)
M|B2C |it|Clear "continue cancelling" at every step
M|B2C |**Ty|** 20-30%
M|B2C |**Ex|**
M|B2C |tx|1. "What's the main reason?" → 6 options
M|B2C |tx|2. Selected "Too expensive" → "Get 25% off for 3 months (save $21.75)"
M|B2C |tx|3. Declined → "Or switch to our Starter plan at $12/mo"
M|B2C |tx|4. Declined → "We're sorry to see you go. Your access continues until [date]."
M|B2C |tx|---
M|B2B |tx|Lower volume, higher stakes. Personal outreach is worth the cost.
M|B2B |**Fl|**
M|B2B |tx|```
M|B2B |tx|Cancel button → Exit survey → Offer (or rt to CS) → Confirm → Post-cancel
M|B2B |tx|```
M|B2B |**Ch|**
M|B2B |it|rt accounts above MRR threshold to cs sc
M|B2B |it|Show team impact ("Your 8 team members will lose access")
M|B2B |it|Offer admin-to-admin call for enterprise accounts
M|B2B |it|Longer consideration — allow "schedule a call" as a save option
M|B2B |it|Require admin/owner role to cancel (not any team member)
M|B2B |**Ty|** 30-45% (higher bc of personal touch)
M|B2B |**MR|**
M|B2B |tx|\| Account MRR \| Cancel Flow \|
M|B2B |tx|\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|B2B |tx|\| <$100/mo \| Automated flow w/ offers \|
M|B2B |tx|\| $100-$500/mo \| Automated + flag for CS follow-up \|
M|B2B |tx|\| $500-$2,000/mo \| rt to CS before cancel completes \|
M|B2B |tx|\| $2,000+/mo \| Block self-serve cancel, require CS call \|
M|B2B |tx|---
M|Free|tx|us cancelling paid to return to free tier. Different ps — they're not leaving, they're downgrading.
M|Free|**Fl|**
M|Free|tx|```
M|Free|tx|Cancel button → "Switch to Free?" pm → Exit survey (if still cancelling) → Offer → Confirm
M|Free|tx|```
M|Free|**Ch|**
M|Free|it|Lead w/ the free tier as the first option (not a save offer)
M|Free|it|Show what they keep on free vs. what they lose
M|Free|it|The "save" is keeping them on free, not losing them entirely
M|Free|it|Track free-tier us for future re-upgrade cg
M|Free|tx|---
M|Mont|it|More price-sensitive, shorter commitment
M|Mont|it|Discount offers work well (20-30% for 2-3 months)
M|Mont|it|Pause is effective (1-2 months)
M|Mont|it|Suggest annual plan at a discount as an alternative
M|Mont|**Of|**
M|Mont|tx|1. Discount (if reason = price)
M|Mont|tx|2. Pause (if reason = not using / temporary)
M|Mont|tx|3. Annual plan switch (if engaged but price-sensitive)
M|Annu|it|Higher commitment, often cancelling for stronger reasons
M|Annu|it|Prorate refund expectations matter
M|Annu|it|Longer save window (they've already paid)
M|Annu|it|Personal outreach more justified (higher LTV at stake)
M|Annu|**Of|**
M|Annu|tx|1. Pause remainder of term (if temporary)
M|Annu|tx|2. Plan adjustment + credit for nx renewal
M|Annu|tx|3. Personal outreach from CS
M|Annu|tx|4. Partial refund + downgrade (better than full refund + cancel)
M|Annu|**Re|**
M|Annu|it|Offer prorated refund if sig time remaining
M|Annu|it|"Pause until renewal" if less than 3 months left
M|Annu|it|Be generous — bad refund experiences cr vocal detractors
M|Annu|tx|---
M|The |Don'|
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|Cancel click → 15% off → Still cancelling → 25% off → Still cancelling → Let them go
M|The |tx|```
M|The |**Ru|**
M|The |it|Maximum 2 discount offers per cancel sn
M|The |it|Never exceed 30% (higher trains cancel-for-discount behavior)
M|The |it|Time-limit discounts (2-3 months, then full price resumes)
M|The |it|Track discount accepters — if they cancel again at full price, don't re-offer
M|The |tx|Pause is often better than a discount bc it doesn't devalue your pd.
M|The |**Im|**
M|The |tx|\| Setting \| Recommendation \|
M|The |tx|\|---------\|---------------\|
M|The |tx|\| Pause duration options \| 1 month, 2 months, 3 months \|
M|The |tx|\| Default selection \| 1 month (shortest) \|
M|The |tx|\| Maximum pause \| 3 months (longer pauses rarely return) \|
M|The |tx|\| During pause \| Keep data, remove access \|
M|The |tx|\| Reactivation \| Auto-reactivate w/ 7-day advance em \|
M|The |tx|\| Repeat pauses \| Allow 1 pause per 12-month period \|
M|The |**Pa|**
M|The |- Da|"Your pause ends in 7 days. We've been busy — here's what's new."
M|The |- Da|"Welcome back tomorrow! Here's what's waiting for you."
M|The |- Da|"You're back! Here's a quick tour of what's new."
M|The |For |
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
M|The |tx|│  Before you go, what abt right-sizing │
M|The |tx|│  your plan?                             │
M|The |tx|│                                         │
M|The |│  C|Pro ($49/mo)                  │
M|The |tx|│                                         │
M|The |tx|│  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐    │
M|The |tx|│  │ Switch to Starter ($19/mo)      │    │
M|The |tx|│  │                                 │    │
M|The |│  │|Projects, integrations  │    │
M|The |│  │|Advanced an,     │    │
M|The |tx|│  │         team features           │    │
M|The |tx|│  │                                 │    │
M|The |tx|│  │ [Switch to Starter]             │    │
M|The |tx|│  └─────────────────────────────────┘    │
