M|Segm|tx|The most effective cancel flows use segmentation to show different offers to different cs.
M|Segm|tx|\| Dimension \| Why It Matters \|
M|Segm|tx|\|-----------\|---------------\|
M|Segm|tx|\| Plan / MRR \| Higher-value cs get personal outreach \|
M|Segm|tx|\| Tenure \| Long-term cs get more generous offers \|
M|Segm|tx|\| Usage level \| hi-usage cs get different messaging than dormant ones \|
M|Segm|tx|\| Billing interval \| Monthly vs. annual need different approaches \|
M|Segm|tx|\| Previous saves \| Don't re-offer the same discount to a repeat canceller \|
M|Segm|tx|\| Cancel reason \| Drives which offer to show (core mapping) \|
M|Segm|**Ne|**
M|Segm|it|They haven't activated. The save is onboarding, not discounts.
M|Segm|- Of|Free onboarding call, setup help, extended trial
M|Segm|- As|"What were you hoping to accomplish?" (learn what's missing)
M|Segm|**En|**
M|Segm|it|They love the pd but can't justify the cost.
M|Segm|- Of|Discount, annual plan switch, downgrade
M|Segm|it|hi save potential
M|Segm|**Do|**
M|Segm|it|They forgot abt you. A discount won't bring them back.
M|Segm|- Of|Pause subscription, "what changed?" conversation
M|Segm|it|lo save potential — focus on learning why
M|Segm|**Po|**
M|Segm|it|They're actively choosing something else.
M|Segm|- Of|Competitive match, feedback call, roadmap preview
M|Segm|it|md save potential — depends on reason
M|Segm|tx|---
